Vice President Joe Biden spoke with Ukrainian President Petro Poroshenko about the situation in eastern Ukraine. They both condemned the violation of the ceasefire by separatist forces supported by Russia in the town of Debaltseve. They also noted that this violation was confirmed by the OSCE. Biden also condemned Russia and the separatists for blocking access to Debaltseve by OSCE monitors, allowing the separatists to continue their attacks. Biden agreed with Poroshenko that if Russia continues to violate the Minsk agreements, the costs to Russia will increase.